    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen I load a gigantic ASM file with NASM code in neovim, the redrawtime is often exceeded. To solve this I try to change `syntax sync minlines=20`, `syntax sync maxlines=100` but this seems to be completely ignored. The highlighting is good at the start of the file and then exceeded the time everywhere else. \n\nCC @clason  @matan-bebop \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nOpen a big assembler file in `nvim --clean` and watch.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`minlines`, `maxlines` have an effect.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, vim is never slowing down even without `minlines` and `maxlines` settings.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nVoid Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nn/a\n\n### Installation\n\nVoid Linux repository",
